description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, dynamic and committed clinical pharmacist with well-developed interpersonal skills to join out innovative clinical pharmacy team within Emergency Medicine service at North West Anglia Foundation Trust, this post will be based at Hinchingbrooke Hospital. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your focus will be to deliver specialised, patient centred clinical pharmacy service to our urgent care division through attendance of consultant led ward rounds and facilitation of safe and rapid discharge process utilising our near patient dispensing and discharge transcribing processes. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will become an essential member of the multidisciplinary team providing pharmaceutical advice to all levels and grades of staff for a wide mix of clinical presentations and experiences in a fast paced environment. You will be part of a friendly proactive Emergency Medicine pharmacy team and be actively supported by a robust team of experienced Medicines Management Technicians.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This opportunity presents the successful candidates with a chance to develop their clinical knowledge across a broad range of specialties. We are fully committed to your personal and professional development to enable you to maximise your impact on patient care and would actively support the non-medical prescribing qualification, subject to funding and identified service need.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ola Akinsola:Specialist Pharamcist - Emergency Medicine&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;olabowale.akinsola@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01480 416144&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
